\paragraph{Rope Head Dimension.}
An important insight of M$^2$LA is that the dimensions saved by dynamically sizing the latent space can be traded for a larger RoPE dimension to improve model performance. In prior implementations such as DeepSeek‑MLA and related work, the RoPE head dimension is typically set to 64, whereas the NoPE head dimension is kept at the full head size (128) due to the presence of up‑projection matrices, yielding a total head dimension of 192. We hypothesize that a larger RoPE head better preserves performance. Moreover, recent studies\cite{Step325,hu2025multi} suggest that increasing the overall head dimension enhances expressivity; since the NoPE part is fixed, a larger RoPE head invariably implies a larger total head dimension. We therefore evaluate RoPE head dimensions in $\{16, 32, 64, 128\}$ while keeping the sum of RoPE and latent dimensions constant, reporting both PPL and MMPPL. The results in Table~\ref{tab:ablation_rope_head_dim} corroborate our hypothesis.
